SIMPLE: ere
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ere
<hw>Ere</hw> <pr>(⟦amac⟧r <it>or</it> ⟦acir⟧r; 277)</pr>, <pos>prep. &
adv.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>⟦aemac⟧r</ets>, prep., adv., & conj.; akin to
OS., OFries., & OHG. <ets>⟦emac⟧r</ets>, G. <ets>eher</ets>, D.
<ets>eer</ets>, Icel. <ets>⟦amac⟧r</ets>, Goth. <ets>air</ets>.
⟦root⟧204. Cf. <er>Early</er>, <er>Erst</er>, <er>Or</er>,
<pos>adv.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Before; sooner than.</def>
<mark>[Archaic or Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Myself was stirring <qex>ere</qex> the break of day.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Ere</qex> sails were spread new oceans to explore.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sir, come down <qex>ere</qex> my child die.</q> <rj><qau>John iv.
49.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Rather than.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will be thrown into Etna, . . . <qex>ere</qex> I will leave
her.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ere long</b></col>, <cd>before, shortly.</cd>
<au>Shak.</au> -- <col><b>Ere now</b></col>, <cd>formerly,
heretofore.</cd> <au>Shak.</au> -- <mcol><col><b>Ere that</b></col>,
⟦and⟧ <col><b>Or are</b></col></mcol>. <cd>Same as <er>Ere</er>.</cd>
<au>Shak.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ere</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ere
<hw>Ere</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To plow.
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> See <er>Ear</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos></def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erebus</ent>⟦br⟧
